<div id="section">
<h2>Pharmacy</h2>
<p>
The Department was set up in 1998 and is being run by one full time Consultant 
and two full time Specialists. The department provides consultation in the Out 
Patient and offers electro-cautry services for various minor dermato surgical 
problems. Facility for the cautry of viral warts is available on the latest 
Italian cautry machine- Epilodine. On an average 150-160 patients get consultation 
in the morning and 20-30 in the evening. The department is conducting a study on 
incidence of unwanted hair growth (HIRSUTISM) in females and efficacy of various 
treatment modalities.The Department plans Cryosurgery and Laser hair-removal technique.</p>
 
Sahib Memorial Trust started providing Psychiatric care to patients in August 1996. 
The present team of Mental Health professionals comprises of  Psychiatrists, a 
Clinical Psychologist and a Medical Officer. They provide consultancy to out 
patients only.The Department of Psychiatry provides psychotherapeutic intervention 
to people with psycho-social, emotional, behavioural and interpersonal problems. 
The Counselling room is equipped with diagnostics tests.Due to  heavy inflow of 
patients during morning time, Pyschiatric services have been started in the 
evening OPD since October 2001.</p>

Later Mr. Ibrar A. Mumtaz, Mr. Shahid Hussain, Chaudhry Ahmad Saeed, 
Mr. Mohammad Munir Chaudhry and Mr. Altaf M. Saleem joined the Trust. Now the 
Trust comprises of seven members and is working under the leadership of Chaudhry 
Ahmad Saeed since April 1996. Their active support and cooperation has played an 
instrumental role in bringing this institute at par with international standards 
of tertiary care teaching hospital.
</p>
